Document 2: NARRATIVE_DESIGN_PHILOSOPHY.md (Unabridged)
Purpose: Explain why the Sydney/Oswaldo narrative engine works—the design theory behind behavior-first storytelling, choice-cost architecture, and how to avoid AI failure modes in emotional narrative.

Sections Covered:

The 17 Lessons as Behavioral Observations (directionality: behavior-first vs theme-first)
The Choice-Cost Archetype Framework (5 resource types)
The "Hallmark Card" Problem (and fixes)
Discipline as Design (lesson labeling rubric + priority order)
Uniqueness Analysis (what's uncommon about this system)
Key Concepts:

Directionality (Behavior-First vs Theme-First):

Theme-First (standard): Start with abstract theme ("this is about grief"), build scenes to point at it. AI fails here by writing summary commentary instead of dramatization.
Behavior-First (this project): Start with concrete behavior pattern. Let the theme emerge naturally. Example: Room paid before anyone knew it was due → Oswaldo says "what did you do today?" → Lesson 6 "Invisibility of Competence" is now visible through behavior, not narration.
Why 17 Lessons Work (Overlapping Cameras):

17 lessons = 17 different camera angles on the same room without redundancy
Lesson 1 (Load-Bearing Beams): "the weight itself"
Lesson 6 (Invisibility of Competence): "why nobody sees the weight"
Lesson 7 (This Isn't Hard): "why they conclude the weight doesn't exist"
Each lesson can touch 2-3 without forcing any—this is why tie-break rule exists
5 Resource Types (Choice-Cost Archetype):

Money (cash on hand, debt capacity)
Dignity (self-respect, swallowing pride)
Relationship (burning capital with Oswaldo/Trina/Dex)
Safety (physical risk, exposure, stability)
Time (sleep, deadlines, urgency)
Every choice must spend a DIFFERENT, non-fungible currency. Can't convert dignity to money. Sydney has $47, needs $65—this is a resource allocation problem with no good answers.

Double Duty as Quality Gate: This turns subjective quality ("Are choices meaningful?") into objective verification ("Do choices represent distinct cost types?"). If AI generates 3 choices that all cost the same thing = detectable failure.

Scene Template Cost Structures:

Rising Tension: one practical move, one emotional move, one delay move (each hurts differently)
Confrontation: one hard line, one strategic retreat, one redirect
Breaking Point: one self-protective rupture, one costly compromise, one structural boundary
The Hallmark Card Problem (Default AI Failure):
Sincerity without specificity. Model knows emotions are supposed to sound like, produces text that gestures at feeling without earning it.

Bad: "Sydney felt a wave of exhaustion."
Good: "You've been awake since 5. He asked what's for breakfast."
Fixes:

Show-Don't-Tell Examples - don't just say "show, don't tell"; give bad output vs good output with structural differences labeled
Banned Phrasing List - "The lesson is...", "What this teaches us...", "In the end, she realized...", therapy-speak. Act as canaries.
Discipline as Design (Priority Order for Conflicts):

Continuity (facts are sacred)
Character (consistency gates possibility)
Agency (choices must matter)
Style (prose quality comes last)
When style conflicts with continuity, style LOSES. This makes quality failures diagnosable.

Lesson Labeling Rubric (Functional Definition):

Use null when scene is logistical, atmospheric, or transitional
Use numeric lesson ONLY when one conflict drives the scene AND lesson is visible in behavior
Tie-breaker: Choose lesson that changed Sydney's OPTIONS the most in this specific scene
Uniqueness (What's Uncommon Here):

Voice Translation Layers - translate state ("oswaldoAwareness=0") into prose BEFORE model sees it, exploiting model's tendency to mirror input register
Choice-Cost Typing - game design constraint applied to narrative (define by resource cost)
Negative Constraints as Quality Functions - define valid output by what is REJECTED (banned phrases, repetition rules)
Post-Hoc Labeling with Tie-Breaks - write first, label after, using functional definitions not semantic ones
Conclusion: Treating AI fiction as a SYSTEMS DESIGN problem, not a prompt engineering problem. Built a "narrative compiler" where "good" is structurally defined and mechanically verifiable.

Actionable Content: This is the DESIGN BIBLE. When you disagree about narrative direction, reference this. When a choice feels weak, check: does it spend a different currency? When Sydney reacts oddly, check: is the behavior visible or is it narrated? When AI output feels preachy, check: did it do the "Hallmark Card" failure?

Connections: This explains WHY the WRITING_STYLE_REFERENCE rules work. It's the scaffolding that holds the voice stable under AI generation. VOICE_ANALYSIS_BEST_WORST shows what happens when these principles are violated.

