Document 9: NARRATIVE_QA_STRATEGY.md
Purpose: Strategy for enforcing narrative quality in CI/CD without relying on "vibes." Two-layer gate: Runtime Sanity (deterministic, fast) + CI Evaluation (probabilistic, deep).

Sections Covered:

The Two-Layer Gate (overview)
Layer 1: Runtime Sanity (Bouncer) - 5 checks
Layer 2: CI Evaluation (Critic) - 5 metrics
Test Types (4 categories)
Why This Works
Layer 1 - Runtime Sanity (Deterministic, Zero Tolerance):

5 Structural Checks:

Schema Validity - JSON structure, field types
Choice Count - Exact (3 for normal, variable for endings)
Banned Phrases - Regex rejection: "The lesson is...", therapy-speak, moralizing
Word Count - Warn @ 280 / Fail @ 350 (normal); Warn @ 370 / Fail @ 450 (endings)
Apology Loops - Detection of AI refusal/apology patterns
Layer 2 - CI Evaluation (Probabilistic, Deep):

5 Quality Metrics (1-5 scale or Boolean):

Voice Fidelity (1-5) - Does Oswaldo sound distinct from narrator?
Cost Distinctness (Boolean) - Do 3 choices spend different currencies?
Didactic Slips (Boolean) - Does narrative summarize theme? ("She realized...")
Sensory Detail (Boolean) - At least one concrete physical detail?
Continuity Callback (Boolean) - References past thread/fact?
Evaluator Process:

Input: Generated Scene + Rubric
Output: Structured JSON ({ voiceFidelity: 4, costDistinct: true, ... })
Action: Fail build if voice fidelity < 3 OR cost distinctness = false. Warn on others.
Test Types (4 Categories):

Adversarial Fixtures - Handcrafted BAD scenes that MUST trigger rejection (e.g., scene with "The lesson is...")
Golden Fixtures - Handcrafted GOOD scenes that MUST pass (prevents over-tuning)
Translation Map Coverage - Verify every thread value has voice translation entry
Transition Bridge Map - Verify all bridges connect valid states
Why This Works:

Heuristics catch machine failures (broken JSON, refusal loops)
Evaluators catch artistic failures (boring prose, generic voice) that regex can't see
Actionable Content: This is the QUALITY GATE ARCHITECTURE. Layer 1 is automated in the provider. Layer 2 is automated in CI. Use this to understand what gets rejected and why.

